dcterms:description: The CoNLL-2012 dataset is used for semantic role labeling and contains gold predicates and parse information for each sentence, which are utilized to define hard constraints for the SRL task.
dcterms:title: CoNLL-2012

dcterms:creator: Paul Kingsbury
Martha Palmer
dcterms:description: PropBank provides a corpus of texts annotated with information about basic semantic propositions, which are used in conjunction with syntactic parse trees from the Penn Treebank.
dcterms:title: PropBank

dcterms:description: OntoNotes v5.0 is a comprehensive dataset that includes annotations for various linguistic phenomena, including semantic roles, which are essential for semantic role labeling tasks.
dcterms:title: OntoNotes v5.0

dcterms:creator: Mitchell P Marcus
Mary Ann Marcinkiewicz
Beatrice Santorini
dcterms:description: The Penn Treebank is a large annotated corpus of English that provides syntactic parse trees, which are used in conjunction with semantic role annotations from PropBank and OntoNotes.
dcterms:title: Penn Treebank
